Main text <attbytes>204Kb</attbytes><display>No</display><reflink></reflink><comcitn><ty>BOOK</ty><id>Z200767884</id><a1>Drinkwater, John, 1882&ndash;1937</a1><t1>A Man's House: A Play in Three Acts</t1><pbl>Sidgwick &amp; Jackson, Ltd.</pbl><y1>1934</y1><t2>Literature Online</t2></comcitn></comhd2>
<div3>
<comhd3><idref>Z300767885</idref><collection>1 2</collection>
ACT I <attbytes>82Kb</attbytes><display>1</display><reflink></reflink><comcitn><ty>BOOK</ty><id>Z300767885</id><a1>Drinkwater, John, 1882&ndash;1937</a1><t1>A Man's House: A Play in Three Acts</t1><pbl>Sidgwick &amp; Jackson, Ltd.</pbl><y1>1934</y1><t2>Literature Online</t2></comcitn></comhd3>
<stage><p><hi r="italic">Salathiel's house in Jerusalem. A terrace on the upper floor, looking out on to the hills. Esther is seated on the terrace. There is a sound of sheep bells, and music from a pipe. It is a fine spring evening</hi>.</p>
<p><hi r="italic">Esther, who is blind, comes into the room, feeling her way for a needlework frame. She is twenty&hyphen;seven&mdash;rather restless&mdash;acutely sensitive always to the immediate circumstance and emotion of her environment. Not weak at all, but not withdrawn to any fortress of her own in her blindness. She returns to her seat</hi>.</p>
<p><hi r="italic">Suddenly the quiet is broken by the stormy voice of Salathiel, a prosperous, impressive merchant of fifty&hyphen;five. A pillar of the established order, with disturbing elements of liberal thought in his mind</hi>.</p></stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Rachel! Rachel! <stage>(<hi r="italic">Entering</hi>)</stage> Ah&mdash;Esther, my dear&mdash;<stage>(<hi r="italic">His voice softens</hi>)</stage> Where is Rachel?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>How should I know?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">a propitiatory hand on her shoulder</hi>).</stage> <p>No&mdash;no, of course not. <stage>(<hi r="italic">Back into the room</hi>)</stage> But where is she?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="8">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Probably she's gone out.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>That's just it. I won't have her going out.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Well, don't scold me. I'm not to blame.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>No&mdash;no&mdash;of course not, my dear&mdash;I'm not scolding you. But I won't have it. She was in the garden ten minutes ago, and now, when I go to speak to her, she's gone.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">The piping stops</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>I expect it's David.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>That's it. David. Running about with him like this. It's shameless.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>It's your own fault. You spoil her.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I do not.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes you do. It's always been the same.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I've told her over and over again I won't have it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes&mdash;and a lot of notice she takes.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I can't lock her up.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Why not?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Don't be ridiculous&mdash;my dear. She's a grown woman.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>She's a spoilt child.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Well, what am I to do?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Be master in your own house.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I am master. I always have been. Your mother, God rest her, knew that.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Rachel is different. Or she thinks she is. She needs teaching.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>If it were some respectable young <pb n="9">fellow I shouldn't mind so much. But this David&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">appearing at the room entrance</hi>).</stage> <p>What about David?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>And where have you been?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">nineteen&mdash;fiery&mdash;self&hyphen;possessed&mdash;with all the power of young beauty</hi>).</stage> <p>In the garden, talking to Uncle Nathan.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I didn't see you. I came out to look for you.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I know.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Did you know I was looking for you?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Now don't be peevish, there's a darling.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I'm not a darling&mdash;I won't be a darling.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Of course you will. There now. What is it&mdash;about David?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I strongly disapprove&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Uncle Nathan says&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I don't care what Uncle Nathan says&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>But Uncle Nathan is very wise&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">sharply</hi>).</stage> <p>Don't contradict your father.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>It's all right, my dear&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Very well. Go on spoiling her.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>He doesn't spoil me. Do you? What's the fuss about? David's as good as we are, isn't he?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Socially, I've no objections to offer. But his political views make him quite ineligible. You belong to an old and honoured family in Jerusalem. <stage>(<hi r="italic">Breaking out</hi>)</stage> I tell you I won't have <pb n="10">you mixing yourself up with people who are a menace to everything valuable and respected among us. I admit that there's plenty of room for reform in Jerusalem, and I wish to do injustice to no one. But this young man is notorious. He sets his own people at defiance. I have spoken to his father who, I may tell you, disapproves&mdash;very strongly&mdash;of his son's conduct.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>But what has David done?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Done? You know very well.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Always hanging about that Nazarene.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>You needn't call him &ldquo;that Nazarene&rdquo; like that. His name is Jesus.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Don't be impertinent.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I'm sorry, Esther.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>You used to be such a sensible child. And now you want to go upsetting everything.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I don't want to upset anything. But what's the use everyone getting into a state just about somebody else's opinions? Jesus doesn't want to upset anyone.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>My child, you are mistaken. He wants to destroy the foundations upon which we live.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>No, really, father. Uncle Nathan says&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Will you stop saying what your Uncle Nathan says?</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">Nathan comes in. He is a few years older than his brother, rather a wistful, negligent figure, but with a fine, if subdued, challenge in his face</hi>.</stage>
<pb n="11">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>I beg your pardon, Salathiel&mdash;am I interrupting&mdash;?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Not at all. I want a word with you, Nathan. There's a good deal going on in this house to which I object.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Not really?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>What do you mean, not really? I object, I tell you. This girl is getting out of hand.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>I'm sure she's a very good girl.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>That's as may be. She's forgetting things that she ought to remember. That we all ought to remember.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Is she?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes. She is. And you don't help to remind her.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>I'm sorry, Salathiel.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Look here, Nathan, let me be plain. I can put up with a good deal. I think you will allow that I have put up with a good deal.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Of course, Salathiel, you've been very kind to me.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Well, since we're being plain, I have. For fifteen years now I've kept you here, doing nothing but scribble and talk&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Father, please&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Be quiet, Rachel.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>I know&mdash;I know&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Never mind&mdash;I don't complain&mdash;I don't grudge it. The Lord made you that way, and a man can't see his kin starve.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="12">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>You've been very generous&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I don't reproach you. I should never have spoken of it, but for this, now. I don't care what you think, I don't even mind it being said in Jerusalem that Salathiel has a brother in his house who is no credit to the industry and the wisdom of their fathers. Scribble if you must, and talk as you please to those with sense enough to take no notice. But I won't have my child's mind corrupted&mdash;do you understand?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>I love Rachel as I should my own daughter.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Of that you can be no judge. I don't wish to be hard, but I must be firm. This young man David is a follower of the Nazarene. I forbid my daughter to be contaminated by such an acquaintance, and I forbid you to encourage her.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>But have you heard Jesus of Nazareth speak?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I have not. Nor shall I. His doctrines are pernicious.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>No, Salathiel. He preaches love.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>He preaches the overthrow of the temple. He denies order. He is a maker of sedition.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>When I listen to him, I ask myself, how if this should be Messiah?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">genuinely shocked</hi>).</stage> <p>That is blasphemy. Messiah is to found a kingdom. But I won't dispute with you. You know my will. Respect it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="13">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>This love you talk about, Uncle Nathan; you don't really believe in that, do you?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>When he tells of it, I think I do.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>A God of love? That's splendid, isn't it? <stage>(<hi r="italic">With sudden violence</hi>)</stage> Who made me blind?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>My dear&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>No&mdash;don't be sympathetic for God's sake&mdash;if there is a God. I'm sick of pity. For ten years now I've lived on it. Ever since that day when it happened&mdash;you've all been so considerate. What's the good of it? <stage>(<hi r="italic">Rising</hi>)</stage> Why should I be blind? You all think I've been so submissive&mdash;poor Esther&mdash;so brave, isn't she? Well, I'm not submissive&mdash;I'm not brave&mdash;I hate the God who did it to me. And now in my torment I have to endure this new chatter in the house about a God of love.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes&mdash;yes, my dear&mdash;it's unreasonable. But you mustn't let it trouble you like this&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Then tell them to stop it&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">to the others</hi>).</stage> <p>You see&mdash;nothing but grief comes of it all.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">moving to her</hi>).</stage> <p>I'm sorry, Esther, I didn't know you felt like that.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Let's say no more about it. I apologise for making a scene.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>The other day I heard Jesus say&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I won't have his words spoken in this house.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="14">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>And yet you have seemed lately, Salathiel, to be so much more liberal in your mind. Your work among the poor&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Perhaps&mdash;but it's no time for tolerance when the foundations of society are threatened. This man threatens them. <stage>(<hi r="italic">Moving on to the terrace</hi>)</stage> Esther, my dear, I'm sorry that this should have happened. Go on with your sewing.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Thank you. Pity the poor blind child.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Now, now&mdash;you mustn't talk like that.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">He looks out over the balustrade</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">A Voice from the road below</hi>.</speaker> <p>Ah, good evening, Salathiel.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Good evening, Levi.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>Have you heard?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>What?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>About this Nazarene fellow?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>No&mdash;what? Come up.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">He moves to the room entrance, and a moment later receives Levi&mdash;a prosperous, well&hyphen;established merchant like himself</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">shaking hands</hi>).</stage> <p>I don't like the look of it at all. Good evening, Esther&mdash;Rachel.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther and Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Good evening.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">stiffly</hi>).</stage> <p>Good evening, Nathan.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Good evening, Levi.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>Busy?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>No&mdash;not very.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>We all have to keep at it in these times.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, Levi.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="15">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>What is it now?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>I had to send one of my clerks out to Bethany this morning on business&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes. Sit down. Some wine?</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">They sit on the terrace, glasses before them. Nathan and Rachel stand apart</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>Thank you. I was saying&mdash;to Bethany. He has just come back. He saw the Nazarene at an inn, with the men he calls his disciples. They were talking. My boy took a place near them. There was a good deal of the conversation that he couldn't understand. But it seems that they are coming into Jerusalem to&hyphen;morrow. There were many strangers in Bethany&mdash;they seemed to be his followers.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Oho&mdash;a sort of triumphal entry, eh?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>Well now, that's the strange thing about it. He heard this Jesus say that he should ride in on an ass. Two of them were to have one in readiness.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">to Nathan</hi>).</stage> <p>What about Messiah now?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>But that's just like him.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>Of course, it's all absurd, but my clerk felt uneasy about it. So do I. He says that as he sat listening, it was&mdash;mysterious somehow&mdash;the sense of power. There's a lot of unrest in Jerusalem. I don't think you altogether realise it, Salathiel, but it's dangerous.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I noticed something of the kind to&hyphen;day. Loafers at the street corners&mdash;people in the yards, whispering.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="16">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>It's my opinion that there's some sort of conspiracy.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>But there has never been anything underhand in his methods.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>All revolution is underhand. And a kind of revolution is going on.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Depend upon it. I was just saying so.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>I only hope the Council is alive to the danger. This entry into Jerusalem may mean trouble.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>It's the Governor's business. <stage>(<hi r="italic">Rising</hi>)</stage> I shall go down and speak to him.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">Mathias, his son, comes in. He is twenty&hyphen;five, a prim, precise, well&hyphen;groomed specimen of the successful young business man. He is in a state of well&hyphen;disciplined excitement</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Look here, father, something has got to be done about it. Oh&mdash;good&hyphen;evening everybody. There's going to be the devil of a mess to&hyphen;morrow if we don't look out.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>What is it now?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>I've told you about it for months past. And now it's happened&mdash;or nearly. There's a whole gang of them up at Bethany, and they're coming down into Jerusalem to&hyphen;morrow.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I know.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>What's the use of knowing unless we do something? All the hotheads and light&hyphen;wits in the town are boiling up to meet them.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="17">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>All right, my son&mdash;I was just leaving to see the Governor&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes&mdash;when the damage is done&mdash;or ready to be done&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Please remember that you are speaking to your father&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>All right&mdash;I'm sorry&mdash;but I've been looking round. I suspected that something was up&mdash;and I've been going through the city&mdash;I tell you it's everywhere&mdash;gossip, strange faces, furtive figures in the shadows, keys being turned in doors.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>A conspiracy&mdash;I said so.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>The Governor will know how to deal with it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Well, I'm for taking no chances. I've told Reuben that our premises won't be open to&hyphen;morrow&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>You had no right&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>I'm in the business, aren't I? I've had the place boarded up, too.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>It's absurd to be alarmed&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>I tell you it isn't absurd. You are too lenient in your opinions, father. I don't want to see our business wrecked by a rabble. This Nazarene is very quiet in his ways&mdash;it's part of his policy&mdash;but the people take a great deal more notice of him than you think. If he makes any kind of demonstration to&hyphen;morrow, take my word for it the town will be in an uproar.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>He will make no demonstration.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="18">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Oh, I know about his humility and all that. But his sort of humility can be a demonstration in itself&mdash;a very infectious one. If the guards aren't under proper orders to&hyphen;morrow, the consequences may be damned unpleasant.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Do you want to come with me to the Governor?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>No. Only give it him straight. I know what I'm talking about.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>You had better come, Levi. Your information will be valuable.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes. <stage>(<hi r="italic">To all</hi>)</stage> Good&hyphen;night.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Salathiel and Levi go out</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>It's the devil. Just when things were improving all round. These agitators want to be made to work for a bit. A year or two on the galleys would teach them something.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>It seems to me you're easily scared.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Of course you'd stand up for them. That's your friend David. A good stiff job of work would do him no harm either.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>David believes in this new gospel. He wants to make that his work.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Gospel my foot. He's teaching idlers to be dissatisfied, that's all about it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Oh, no, Mathias, it isn't like that at all. He wants everyone to work, in peace.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>It's all very well, Uncle Nathan&mdash;but you don't know what work is. Here I've stuck to it every day since I grew up&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="19">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, I know, you've been a very industrious boy&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Never mind about that. I've brought new energy, new brains into father's business&mdash;I'm making a career for myself. If a man has ability and works hard and uses his wits there's a good future for him to&hyphen;day, so long as the foundations of society are kept firm. This fellow wants to shake them, or break them. He wants to do away with character and purpose and power. Do you know what he said the other day? &ldquo;Blessed are the meek, for they shall inherit the earth&rdquo;&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, I heard him say it&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Well, what kind of stuff is that to talk? Of course, if you want to put it in your poetry or whatever it is, it doesn't matter. But this is different. This man isn't a poet, a dreamer. He's a politician, and if you bring that sort of nonsense into politics, where are our foundations then?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Mathias is right. Authority can't be maintained like that.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Whose authority?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Any authority. Order. Discipline. Keeping people in their places.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>But so many people have no place at all&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>That's their look out&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Only a lot of poor&hyphen;spirited creatures&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>That was another thing he said&mdash;<pb n="20">&ldquo;Blessed are the poor in spirit, for theirs is the Kingdom of Heaven.&rdquo;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Well, I say let the kingdom of Heaven look after itself. What I want is to make something of my kingdom on earth, and I'm not going to have my chances queered by a peddling moralist if I can help it. If he creates a row to&hyphen;morrow, I hope they'll get him.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>The city gates ought to be closed. A nice commotion this road will be if they are allowed to come in.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>It will be all right.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>They won't molest us, if that's what you mean, but I've no fancy for dirty mobs.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>That's it&mdash;a dirty mob.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>You never saw such peace as was among the multitude when he spoke upon the Mount.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Why don't you go and join him, Uncle Nathan?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Esther!</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>I am too old to have the courage. I cling to my shelter here.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Look here, Uncle Nathan, I don't mind your living on us&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Mathias, you can't talk like that.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Can't I? Well, I can. It's the plain truth&mdash;Uncle Nathan doesn't bring a penny to the house. Very well. But he has no right to talk about something that threatens us all as though it didn't matter.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="21">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">out on the terrace</hi>).</stage> <p>Look&mdash;what a lovely night it is.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>I can't look.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>No, dear. But it is lovely. The hills are like agate. Not a breath among the palms. And the Bethany road up there is so clear. Not a movement anywhere. Just two men passing over, leading an ass with a foal. The stars are coming out.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Levi said so. Two, he said, had been sent&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Charming. An essay in necromancy. But the stars are blind, too.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Stop it. Light those lamps, Rachel.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Rachel does so</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">rising and coming in from the terrace</hi>).</stage> <p>It is getting cold. Draw the shutters.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">She takes a seat in the room as Rachel closes out the terrace</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>I'm going down to look round again. Get me my cloak, Rachel.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Rachel goes out, Mathias following</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Esther, my dear, I am grieved for you.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Spare your grief, old Uncle. I don't need it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>But you do, child.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Have some wine.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Your father offered me none.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>He was troubled.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>It is a little thing. <stage>(<hi r="italic">He takes it</hi>.)</stage> This blindness&mdash;it is so terrible?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="22">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Living, I am dead.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>You said that the stars were blind. But we all are.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>That's your silly poetry. Blind has one meaning only. No eyes. Darkness&mdash;the world shut out&mdash;no colour&mdash;no light&mdash;just death before the tomb.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>You, too, think of me as a burden&mdash;a tax upon the house.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>I suppose so. And yet I used to read verses&mdash;once&mdash;when I was able to&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>I know&mdash;&ldquo;The Lord doth build up Jerusalem: he gathereth together the outcasts of Israel&rdquo;&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">defensively</hi>).</stage> <p>Why do you say that&mdash;now? What have we&mdash;what have I to do with the outcasts?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Jesus is the friend of the outcasts. If I could make you understand that, Esther, my dear.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>I am no outcast.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>No?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>No? Why, no? No, I tell you.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Cast into the outer darkness?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Darkness? Why do you speak of darkness? Oh God, how utterly, utterly dark.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>I, too, am in darkness.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>You do not know.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Oh yes, I know. Your father&mdash;Mathias&mdash;even you, my child&mdash;you take me for a poor old <pb n="23">vexation. Only Rachel knows, she knows what I know. She knows the light that keeps us.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Uncle Nathan, are you really mad?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Maybe. &ldquo;I will sing a new song unto thee, O God; upon a psaltery and an instrument of ten strings will I sing praises unto thee.&rdquo; You remember that, too&mdash;before the darkness came?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>You sit ten hours a day on that everlasting terrace, and see what new song you'll sing.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>He could give you peace.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>I don't want peace. I want sunlight, movement, lovers. They are denied me, for ever. Do you know what is my one comfort?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>No, my dear.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>That at least I shall never learn resignation. I can do nothing, but my mind shall rebel until the end. If I could be revenged, I would, without mercy. That is all my religion.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>It is a pity.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Must you be so infernally sweet about it? Why don't you tell me not to be the ill&hyphen;conditioned wench you think I am?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>My dear&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Oh yes, you do. Only you pity me, like all the rest. More than they&mdash;you're so damned considerate&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Esther darling&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>I know&mdash;I'm an outrageous devil. Sometimes I think there really is a devil in me. I keep him very quiet&mdash;but he's there, brooding, waiting <pb n="24">on who knows what. He is restless to&hyphen;night. If I could send him out to trap this Nazarene, so smug with his loving one another. <stage>(<hi r="italic">A pause</hi>.)</stage> Were you ever in love, Uncle Nathan?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>With whom?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Your mother.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Did she know?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>I think so. Yes.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>What did you do about it?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Nothing.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Was she in love with you?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, my child.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>And you did nothing. Good God! Tell me&mdash;Rachel's David is a fine boy to look at, isn't he?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Splendid.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>A comely person&mdash;like that other David, eh? If I could steal him&mdash;even just for once&mdash;do you think I would hesitate?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Esther&mdash;Esther&mdash;it is miserable to see you so&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>It wounds your tender heart&mdash;I know. Only I'ld like someone to understand it&mdash;all scruples have been burnt out of me.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>You say what you don't believe.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Very well.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">Isaac, a rotund and self&hyphen;important house steward appears at the room entrance</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Excuse me, miss, but did the master say when he would be coming back?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="25">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>No, Isaac. What is it?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>I'm having trouble with the servants, miss. At least, with one of them. It's young Jacob.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>What's the matter?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Well, miss, he wants to go out.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Go out? At this time of night?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Just so, miss. He's a very good lad generally, and works hard. But something seems to have come over him. He's quite obstinate. I even threatened to whip him, but it had no effect. He insists.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>But of course he can't go out. It's absurd.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, miss, but he won't take no for an answer. He says he must speak to the master himself.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Well, the master is out.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes. But what am I to do, miss? He's making quite a disturbance.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Put him in his room and lock him up.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>I did attempt something of the sort&mdash;but he just stood and stared at me with a sort of look that&mdash;well, somehow I couldn't.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>My father employs a steward to keep order in his house.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>I know, miss. I blame myself&mdash;but there it is. Besides, miss, good servants are very hard to come by these days.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="26">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Well, you must deal with it. A good servant doesn't want to go out like this without warning.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>There's something quite unusual about it. In my opinion, miss, it has to do with those brothers of his. They're quite a respectable family really&mdash;fishermen, I believe. But two of them have taken up with this travelling preacher everyone talks about, and it's my belief that they've been putting ideas into his head.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Perhaps I could do something.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">coldly</hi>).</stage> <p>I hardly think so, Mr Nathan.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Send him up.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>I beg your pardon, miss&mdash;?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Send him up.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>But&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Do as you're told.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, miss. <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">He goes</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>More of your precious friend's doing.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>I've talked to Jacob several times. An interesting boy.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">Jacob, a fresh, eager, young peasant, is shown into the room by Isaac, who stands at the entrance</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Shall I wait, miss?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, you'd better. What's your name&mdash;Jacob?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, miss.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>What is all this I hear from Isaac?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>I don't know what he's said.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="27">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>That you want to go out, at this time of night.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes&mdash;I must.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Must&mdash;that's no way to talk. Do you want to leave altogether?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>I don't know.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Because if you go like this, you go for good.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>I see.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>You are not ill&hyphen;treated here?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>No, miss.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Is your work too hard?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>No&mdash;it's easy.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>You get good wages, don't you?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>What is it then?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>I must go&mdash;out there&mdash;to Bethany.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>What on earth should you be doing at Bethany?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>I must just be there.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>When did you propose to come back?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>I don't know.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>When did he first speak of this, Isaac?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Only an hour ago&mdash;when I told him to shut the yard gates.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Don't you realise that your conduct is very strange?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>What does it matter&mdash;I'm not important here&mdash;nobody would miss me.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Of course you're not important&mdash;but servants can't come and go just as they please. <pb n="28">Your work is of small consequence, no doubt, but it has to be done.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>I must go to Bethany.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>What for?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>I must be there.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>If it is so serious, why didn't you go without asking?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>I didn't want to be underhand about it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Who is it you want to see there?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>The Master.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Don't be absurd&mdash;the master isn't at Bethany.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>I mean the other Master&mdash;<hi r="italic">the</hi> Master.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>You mean this man Jesus?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes&mdash;the Master.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>How do you know about him?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>I have two brothers who are with him&mdash;Peter and Andrew. Twice I've listened to him myself.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>I thought as much.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Do you know that he is a very dangerous man?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>No, my dear&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Please don't interfere, Uncle Nathan. He's just making people discontented. You see for yourself.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>I didn't feel that about him, miss. He made me feel somehow that I&mdash;I mattered, if you understand. Not grand, or anything like that&mdash;but&mdash;somebody.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="29">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>I know.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>So that now you're too good for your work.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>It isn't that at all. Only I want to learn more from him&mdash;and I've only just heard that he's come to Bethany. They say he's coming into Jerusalem&mdash;right among all the people who hate him. They are afraid of him really, but they may do something. I must be with him.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>To protect him&mdash;is that it?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>You may laugh, miss. But I tell you it's something I can't argue about. I know that I must go&mdash;that's all.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>I'm very sorry, miss, you should be bothered like this.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>And what do you expect to do afterwards?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>I can't tell anything about it. May I go, please?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Let him go, Isaac. Understand, of course, that you get no wages.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>I don't want any wages.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>And you needn't come back.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>I see, miss.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Esther, my dear, surely&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Please, Uncle Nathan&mdash;<stage>(<hi r="italic">To Jacob</hi>)</stage> You can go.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>I might get a chance of speaking to him&mdash;sometimes he talks to anybody. If I do, I'll say you let me come. <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">He goes out aflame</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="30">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Of course, if you think it's all right, miss&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>It's no good keeping lunatics in the house.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>No, miss. So long as you take the responsibility.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>That will do, Isaac.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, miss. <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">He goes</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Light&hyphen;headed&mdash;that's all about it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Couldn't you feel the truth shining out of him, though?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>What has throwing up a good situation and going off without a penny after an imposter got to do with truth?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>I understood just what he meant, though. You can't describe it. There is something about this man that is quite new&mdash;unlike all the old doctrine. It's as though he were beginning all over again&mdash;laying fresh foundations&mdash;asking us to search our hearts&mdash;to put away pretence.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>What has that to do with us? This is a world of conflict, of suspicions and angers and betrayals. What we need is defence, and power. It is an imposture, I tell you.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>It will come, maybe&mdash;after many days.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Rachel comes in</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>What has happened to the boy Jacob?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>He has left, that's all.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I saw him going across the yard, running, all eager. I called out, asking him where he was <pb n="31">going, and he said, to Bethany <stage>(<hi r="italic">opening the terrace partition and looking out</hi>).</stage> There he is, running up the hill. Why is he going to Bethany?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>To join his brothers.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>They are with Jesus of Nazareth.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>What is it to&hyphen;night, Uncle Nathan? Something seems to be moving&mdash;everywhere.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>It's a full moon&mdash;it unsteadies weak wits.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Isaac returns</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">at the entrance</hi>).</stage> <p>I don't know what's happening to&hyphen;night, miss. It's that Mr David now&mdash;says he must see Miss Rachel. I told him what time it is. I did more&mdash;I ventured to remind him that he's not received at this house. I even made to shut the door in his face, but he pushed his way in. I told him I would fetch the master or Mr Mathias&mdash;he said he knew they were both out. What am I to do now, miss?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David's voice</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">as he comes up the stairs</hi>).</stage> <p>Rachel&mdash;Rachel!</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">He brushes Isaac aside as he comes into the room. He is red&hyphen;haired, glowing with athletic beauty and strength</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>David&mdash;you shouldn't come here.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>I had to.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>You chose your time cautiously, when my father and brother were away. That was honourable of you.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">simply</hi>).</stage> <p>Please don't talk like that. I had to see Rachel&mdash;I took the chance. There's <pb n="32">never been a night like this. Rachel, dear&mdash;Jesus is at Bethany&mdash;he's coming into the city.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I know.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>All of us who love him have waited months for this. It's a challenge.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Well?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>I love you, Rachel&mdash;you know how much I love you. I'm going to join him. I want you to come too. Now.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>You must be stark mad.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>No, no, no&mdash;he said it&mdash;to forsake all and follow him. The time has come. Everyone will have to make a decision. Either we are for him or against him.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>This house is against him.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>You can't speak for Rachel. She has known, all this time. We have to choose between the old life and the new. There's a great crowd gathering up at Bethany. Will you come?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>But that's impossible, David.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>How impossible?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I mean&mdash;to&hyphen;night&mdash;everything here&mdash;how can I leave like that?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Listen. All of life before us depends on one single act of faith, now. If we fail&mdash;if you fail&mdash;everyone you know, all your father's friends, the great ones of Jerusalem, will say you were right. But we shall have lost ourselves.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I have faith, David&mdash;I believe you&mdash;I believe in you. But how can I&mdash;now?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="33">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>There is nothing now to wait for. Tomorrow they will try to break him. Not to be with him now is to deny him. I can't do that.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Uncle Nathan, what am I to do?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>None but you can answer that, my child.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">She opens the terrace partition wide, and stands for a moment looking out on to the hill, now in moonlight. Then</hi>&mdash;</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Uncle Nathan.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, my dear?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I want to ask you something.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">He goes out to her. During the following scene they pass at intervals on their way to and fro along the terrace</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">after a pause</hi>).</stage> <p>David.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, Esther.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>You mustn't take any notice of my sharp temper. Blindness has done that to me.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Please&mdash;I understand.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Come here and sit by me for a minute.</p>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">He takes a place beside her</hi>.</stage>
<p>Tell me something about this Jesus.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Do you really want to know?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>I should like you to tell me.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>He makes everything different. He settles all your quarrels, most of all&mdash;your quarrels with yourself.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Are you sure you're not imagining that in your own mind?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>I don't know. It's there.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="34">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>You'll find it will all blow over&mdash;everything will settle down again&mdash;just as it has always been.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>I don't believe that.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Why do you waste all you might be on a foolish enthusiasm?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>It's nothing like that.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>I think so.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>You don't understand.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, I do. You ought to take a great place in Jerusalem.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>The great places are shams.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>You talk like that now, but it will pass. <stage>(<hi r="italic">A pause</hi>.)</stage> Do you love my sister very much?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>I haven't seen her since she was a child. Is she beautiful?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Very beautiful.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>I was said to be beautiful, too.</p>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">She places her hand on his</hi>.</stage>
<p>Am I?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes. But why do you ask?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Women like to hear it. And I am still a woman. I'm sorry that my father forbids you the house now. It is foolish of him. I'll speak to him if you like. I should like you to come.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">making a movement away from her</hi>).</stage> <p>Please, Esther, don't. <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">He rises</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Oh, very well&mdash;you needn't be so abrupt <pb n="35">about it. If I was crude, remember that I haven't everyone's opportunities.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Esther, I'm sorry, but I can't&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>There's no more to be said. If you want to know the truth, I told my father he would be a fool to let you come here any more. All this Nazarene stuff is no good&mdash;in any case not to us.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>You're strange to&hyphen;night, Esther.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes. It's the devil in me.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">pausing at the terrace opening with Nathan</hi>).</stage> <p>Yes. It is so. <stage>(<hi r="italic">Coming in</hi>)</stage> When are you going, David?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Now&mdash;to&hyphen;night. Are you coming?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>It will be all right for her at Bethany?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes. I have friends. There will be many women.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I will go with you, David.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>I will not allow it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>It must be. Go, David. Wait for me at the foot of the hill. I will be there soon.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>My love!</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">He moves to go. As he does so he is confronted by Mathias</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>You? What is the meaning of this?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>You've come back too soon, Mathias.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Too soon&mdash;what is going on? How dare you come here?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>He has come to take Rachel away with him. To Bethany.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="36">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>To Bethany&mdash;what in God's name are you talking about?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I'm going with David.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>What is the matter with you, girl? Do you know what you're saying?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, Mathias.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">to David</hi>).</stage> <p>Can't you speak? What the devil does this mean?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>That is all. We are going to Bethany.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>You can go to Bethany, or where you will. But Rachel&mdash;is everyone bewitched to&hyphen;night? Isaac has just told me about that fool of a boy. <stage>(<hi r="italic">Flaming&mdash;to David</hi>)</stage> Get out, you scoundrel&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Mathias&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Get out, I tell you.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Please, Mathias, don't&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Get out&mdash;get out&mdash;get out! The town is full of your poison already&mdash;we'll have none of it here.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Mathias&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Don't you speak&mdash;you are shameless. This is an honourable house&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Mathias, my boy&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Have done&mdash;all of you. Will you go?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>I'm going&mdash;but this anger&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Anger! You spread destruction with your insane doctrine, you betray your own people, you defile the law and the word. You creep in here when our backs are turned to steal my sister and seduce her with your dirty treasons&mdash;and I am <pb n="37">not to be angry, if you please! You should be beaten out. <stage>(<hi r="italic">Calling</hi>)</stage> Isaac&mdash;Isaac!</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">going across to him</hi>).</stage> <p>My boy, this helps no one&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Please&mdash;Uncle Nathan&mdash;you have no authority here&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">appearing at the entrance</hi>).</stage> <p>You called, Mr Mathias?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Send this man away, Mathias.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Isaac&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Send him away&mdash;do you hear?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Call your men, Isaac. Give them whips. When this rascal goes, flog him into the street.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>You shan't&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">to Isaac</hi>).</stage> <p>Go. <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Isaac goes</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Why do you destroy your reason?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>See how your pretty gospel bears that&mdash;beaten, you understand?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Do not tempt me.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Oho&mdash;so our loving kindness can be tempted.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Tell those men not to touch me.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>My orders are given. Go whining up to Bethany with your stripes. Tell your Jesus what he has done for you.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Don't speak like that.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Tell him what he, too, may look for.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>I forbid you to say these things&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="38">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Forbid! Tell him that Jerusalem is no place for his corruption&mdash;tell him that we know how to punish his blasphemy&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Mathias&mdash;I implore&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Tell him how we chastise thieves in the night&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Again I&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Tell your rotten&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">David strikes him on the mouth. There is silence for a moment as Mathias recoils, and David stands aghast, staring at his hand. Then</hi>&mdash;</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Oh, my God&mdash;what have I done&mdash;Master! <stage>(<hi r="italic">Almost with a wail</hi>)</stage> Oh&mdash;Master!</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachael</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">going to him</hi>).</stage> <p>David!</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Rachel&mdash;my love&mdash;I have betrayed him.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">He stands, shaken, half sobbing, his head bowed in her arms</hi>.</stage>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">Nathan stands by Esther, who has risen. Salathiel comes in</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>What is this? What are the men below with whips for? Are you all dumb?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>David has been demonstrating the gospel of Nazareth.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Why is he here at all?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">turning to Mathias&mdash;piteously</hi>).</stage> <p>Forgive me, Mathias. I am so utterly ashamed. My faith could not endure one trial.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Go!</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Are you going to Bethany, David?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="39">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Still, I must tell him. He is compassionate.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I am coming with you.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>No&mdash;not now.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Now more than ever.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>I have lost my soul.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>We shall recover it, together.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>What is all this about?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I'm going away with David, father.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>What do you mean?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>It's better to let them go.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, let her go. She is no longer of this house. Let us be clear of them. He has stolen her already.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">passionately</hi>).</stage> <p>Miserable child!</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Isaac returns</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>There is an officer of the Guard below.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes. Bring him.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>And your men will not be needed.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Isaac goes</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Father&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>There is nothing to say.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Isaac shows in a Roman Officer, and goes</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">presenting a paper</hi>).</stage> <p>In the name of C&aelig;sar.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">taking it</hi>).</stage> <p>Yes. I know the business. The Governor told me. I have just left him.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>I think you can all rest easy. Every precaution has been taken. The principal houses on the road in from Bethany will be guarded by <pb n="40">our men. Four have been detailed for duty here. You are to give instructions for them to be admitted at daybreak.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>And no one is to leave the house during the day but yourself. That is your permit.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>In the case of serious trouble, which is unlikely, alarm bells will be rung. In that event the guards have orders to barricade your doors.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>That is all. Good&hyphen;night. <stage>(<hi r="italic">Turning to go</hi>)</stage> Oh&mdash;it's not necessary to ask, but as a matter of form&mdash;you are quite satisfied as to everyone in the house?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Er&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>The servants for example?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes&mdash;the servants are to be trusted.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>Quite so. Good&hyphen;night. <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">He goes</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Why did you not speak?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I was silent for that wretched girl. What now?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>We must go.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>For six generations of men this house has been loyal to itself. And now my daughter forsakes it in the hour of peril.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>If you could but know&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I know. I have loved you, Rachel. It is over. Go <stage>(<hi r="italic">with raised hands</hi>),</stage> and in the name of God may your wrong be visited upon you.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="41">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Salathiel, I have taken much of your charity. I am grateful. But the time has come for me, too, to go. He, the Nazarene, foretold it. &ldquo;I came,&rdquo; he said, &ldquo;not to send peace, but a sword. And a man's foes shall be they of his own household.&rdquo; Come.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">He goes out. Rachel stands for a moment before her father, who does not move; she follows David</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Go to bed, Esther dear.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">after a pause</hi>).</stage> <p>Good&hyphen;night. <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">She goes</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Mathias, tell Isaac that those men will be here at daybreak.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, father. Good&hyphen;night.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Good&hyphen;night. <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Mathias goes</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Sounds come in from the hill&hyphen;side</hi>.</stage>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">Salathiel moves out on to the terrace, and looks out along the road to Bethany. He half cries out</hi> &ldquo;Rachel,&rdquo; <hi r="italic">and checks himself forlornly</hi>.</stage>
<trailer><hi r="smcap">the curtain falls</hi></trailer>
</div3>
<pb n="42">
<div3>
<comhd3><idref>Z300767886</idref><collection>1 2</collection>
ACT II <attbytes>55Kb</attbytes><display>1</display><reflink></reflink><comcitn><ty>BOOK</ty><id>Z300767886</id><a1>Drinkwater, John, 1882&ndash;1937</a1><t1>A Man's House: A Play in Three Acts</t1><pbl>Sidgwick &amp; Jackson, Ltd.</pbl><y1>1934</y1><t2>Literature Online</t2></comcitn></comhd3>
<stage><p><hi r="italic">The same scene. Past noon on the following day. It is bright sunlight</hi>.</p>
<p><hi r="italic">On the terrace are two Roman Guards, motionless, watching the road beyond</hi>.</p>
<p><hi r="italic">Presently Salathiel comes in. He has been dining, and carries a napkin and wine&hyphen;glass. He goes on to the terrace, and stands between the Guards, looking up to Bethany</hi>.</p></stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>No sign of anything?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">First Guard</hi>.</speaker> <p>No, sir.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Looks as though it's going to be a false alarm after all, eh?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">First Guard</hi>.</speaker> <p>I shouldn't wonder, sir.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Second Guard</hi>.</speaker> <p>I said from the first they'ld think better of it when the time came.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>You've no great opinion of this person, then?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Second Guard</hi>.</speaker> <p>Me, sir? Why no. I don't know that he does any particular harm so long as he keeps on the move among the small villages. But we don't want him messing about here, sir, in Jerusalem. There are too many people here looking for trouble. His sort of talk would just suit them.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="43">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>That's a very sensible view to take of it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">First Guard</hi>.</speaker> <p>Excuse my asking, sir, but I suppose you haven't heard anything about the young lady?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>No.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">First Guard</hi>.</speaker> <p>Very sad, her going off like that, sir.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Thank you.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">He comes into the room, and sits dejectedly. After a moment he rises, and walks two or three times across the room, saying</hi> &ldquo;Rachel&rdquo; <hi r="italic">to himself in distress. The shepherd's pipe is heard from the hill&hyphen;side</hi>.</stage>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Esther comes in</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">at the entrance</hi>).</stage> <p>Father, do stop it. Rachel has behaved like a little idiot. Girls have done that before&mdash;they'll do it again. It's no use moaning about it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I know&mdash;she's not worth it. But she was very dear to me.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>You talk as though you had no daughter left.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>You know things don't work that way, Esther, my dear. You must be patient with me.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">sitting</hi>).</stage> <p>I know very well how to be patient.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Giving herself to&mdash;outcasts like that.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Why don't you go out and see what is going on? It would occupy your mind.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">The piping on the hill&hyphen;side ceases</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Nothing is going on. It's long past noon. They must have changed their plans.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="44">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>They probably had warning that it would be safer to stay away.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I daresay that's it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>And yet somehow I don't believe that these people are without courage. I know Rachel is in love with that young man, and I know she is wilful. All the same, it was a brave thing that she did. What made her brave like that?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I don't know. I'm not interested to know. I only know that I have lost her.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>I would have done it myself. But I shouldn't have thought she had it in her.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">sitting</hi>).</stage> <p>You would have done it?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>If I could have found something to believe in enough.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Belief should not have to wait on sudden violence of the mind. It should not be born of a spectacle. It is old, established. There is the God of our fathers, Esther, my dear. He has been a just God. He has given us reputation, riches, honour.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>He has made me blind.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I know, my dear. But we cherish you&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes&mdash;yes. I believe in our God&mdash;when I make myself think about it. But all the rest of the time, I don't really feel that He is with me. He doesn't fill my life, as He ought to, I suppose. Does He yours?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="45">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes&mdash;I think I can say I remember Him always. I have not failed in my duty.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>No, father. But somehow that sounds like a contract&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, an honourable contract. There are laws, and there are rewards and penalties.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>I suppose you are right. You know, father, although sometimes I speak as I shouldn't to you, I really do respect you. I often think how firm and full and decent your life is. The God who gives you that must be a very satisfactory God. I don't wonder that you are roused by any denial of His authority. But it's different with me. I hate all this meddling, too. If no one knows his place, no one will keep it, I see all that. And still, I was jealous of Rachel last night. I'm jealous of her in more ways than one if it comes to that, but I mean jealous of the belief that could make her do what she did. Because, you know, it wasn't just her love for David. It was something shining through David upon her, something shining down from Bethany. I don't know what it is&mdash;if you put it into words, they sound almost like the words of a simpleton, and yet it is something that is larger, more mysterious than the power of our God. I don't feel it&mdash;I only feel that they feel it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>It is not good, my dear, to ask these questions. They can but trouble us.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>I know they trouble us. But sometimes they ask themselves.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="46">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I, too, am sometimes troubled. There is much that is not to be understood. I have tried to be a righteous man, and sometimes I ask myself whether I am not too proud in my righteousness. I seem to have offended none, and yet it may be that my prosperous life is an offence to many. But I do not allow myself to consider these things. The world is not my burden&mdash;it is God's.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>That's just it. How if the world after all should be everybody's burden? Perhaps that is why people go about after this man from Nazareth.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Mathias comes in</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Nothing happening yet?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>No.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">going on to the terrace</hi>).</stage> <p>Why don't you go out, father, and see if you can hear anything?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>There can be nothing to hear, so long as they don't come down from Bethany.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">coming in</hi>).</stage> <p>You know, I've been thinking. They really ought to make an example of this man.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salthiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>At present, he has broken no law.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>No, but if he does come into Jerusalem, it wouldn't be difficult to make him. I think all these precautions to prevent a row are a mistake. If I had my way, I'ld incite a row, and see that he was well in it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>From all accounts, he isn't like that.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Well, if David is anything to go by, his followers are.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="47">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I can't make David out. He always seemed to be such a promising boy.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>I shouldn't worry about him.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>He has Rachel.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Well, we've got to keep a tight hold on ourselves about that. Once you get soft about these things, you lose grip altogether.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I did wrong to let her go away with angry words.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>She could hardly expect a blessing. You were right.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>No, I cannot forget it. It was bitterness&mdash;to my own child. I should have known better than that.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>It's no good, father, you can't have half measures about authority. I'm sorry for Rachel.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>I don't suppose she wants your pity.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>I daresay not, but she has it all the same. I feel this as much as anyone. It's nice for the family, isn't it? There's never been a thing anybody could say against us before. All the same, I'm sorry for the girl&mdash;I like Rachel&mdash;and she's started off her life by making a first&hyphen;rate mess of it. Of course we can't help being sorry for her. But now it's done, it's done, and it's no use for us to lose our nerve about it. People will respect you, father, if you are firm. They won't, if you try to explain as though you had to justify yourself. And they won't, if you weaken and show regrets.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="48">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I wasn't thinking of people's opinions. I was only thinking of Rachel. I would unsay every word to have her back.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Then you really are losing grip. I've never known you like this before. Don't you see, father, that if once we begin to have any doubts about ourselves at a time like this, we're lost? You have brought me up to believe in everything on which Jerusalem has been built&mdash;built by you and the generations before you. It isn't a sudden experiment, about which we are in the dark. It is an old, well&hyphen;tried order, working as fairly for the community as is humanly possible. Under it we know where we are, and what the consequences of our conduct will be for good or bad. These other people can afford to indulge in speculations and idealistic theories&mdash;they'll be no worse off than they were before, if all their fine notions are blown to smithereens. But we stand for a tradition that has taken hundreds of years to work out, and if it falls we fall with it. We can't be philosophical and subtle about it&mdash;we just have a plain duty towards it. It's a simple matter of self&hyphen;protection. What you did about Rachel is what any man in your position ought to have done. If you begin to question it, you might as well throw over the tradition of which you are a part, and have done with it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, boy, you have learnt it well.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>It's your teaching. You can't let me down now.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="49">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I haven't changed. But a new thing has happened to me. Perhaps that is the same as changing, though. I want my girl.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>You have Esther&mdash;and you have me. We are together.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I know, Mathias. You are a good son.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>And Esther, too. When she is&mdash;you know the doctors are hopeful.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Isaac appears at the entrance</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, Isaac, what is it?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Could I speak to you, sir?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes. Alone?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Oh, no, sir, it's all right. The truth is, I'm upset. I know it's not my place to be upset, but I am.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>What about?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>I got talking to one of those Roman guards downstairs. I suppose it was more than I should have done&mdash;but you know what it is, sir, when there's anyone about.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Well?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>It seems he's sometimes on duty at the Governor's house, and hears what is being said.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>You haven't been listening to gossip, Isaac?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>I didn't mean to, sir, but it just came out&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Well&mdash;you don't want me to listen to gossip&mdash;?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>You see, sir, it's about you. Having grown <pb n="50">up here from a boy, sir, I couldn't help taking notice. There was some big gentleman from Rome there the other day, and they were talking about the principal people in Jerusalem. Your name was mentioned, sir. It seems that the big gentleman was saying that the Emperor meant to do something fine for you, and then the Governor said that two or three times lately you had been heard talking as though things might be better than they were in the matter of labour conditions here in Jerusalem, and the big gentleman said that they would have to reconsider it if that was so. Of course, sir, when I was told that, I said straight out that there was no gentleman in Jerusalem with safer opinions than you. But I had to come up and tell you, sir.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>You should give your Roman friend a little advice. If he doesn't keep his tongue still, he'll get into trouble.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, sir. I think he realised he'd said a bit too much.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>And you needn't worry about me, Isaac.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>No, sir. I was sure there couldn't be anything in it. This house has always been an example to the town. But what with that young fool Jacob, and Miss Rachel going off like that, I am a bit jumpy. You'll pardon me, sir.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>That's all right, Isaac.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="51">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Thank you, sir. <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">He goes</hi></stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>There&mdash;you see, father, how little it takes to set people talking.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I've never known anything that would stop people talking.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Well, we can't be too careful&mdash;specially at a time like this. I know it's all nonsense, but we have to be above suspicion. I couldn't bear it if they thought you of all people weren't absolutely sound.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Every act of my life, even up to this last miserable night, is proof enough of my soundness. But I won't always be tongue&hyphen;tied.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">appealingly</hi>).</stage> <p>Please, father, after what happened last night&mdash;I mean Rachel&mdash;do be careful, even about a word.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Very well. <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Isaac returns</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>The Master Barnabas to see you, sir.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Indeed? Show him up.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">A moment later Isaac shows in Barnabas, a sharp&hyphen;featured, rather insignificant little man of something under fifty</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Good afternoon, Barnabas.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>I've been trying to get here all the morning, but I have only just been given my permit. I had great difficulty in getting it at all. In fact, it appeared at one moment that I was actually to be placed under arrest. What are we going to do about it all?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I don't see what there is to be done.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="52">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>What induced you to let her go off with him?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>There was nothing to stop her but force.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>You should have used it. It's been bad enough for me having a son associated with this pernicious movement&mdash;and now there's the scandal of his having run off with a young woman into the bargain.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>They'll be married&mdash;you needn't disturb yourself about that.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>Well, they weren't married last night. In any case it's not what they do, but what people say, and you must have enough sense to know the story that will be made of this&mdash;you ought to have prevented it. My name is ruined.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I've every sympathy with you, Barnabas. But are you abusing me for having my daughter stolen by your son?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>Can't you go and fetch her back or something?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>That's ridiculous.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>Well, I know it's ridiculous, but what am I to do?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>None of us can do anything, except keep our heads.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>Don't you be impudent, young man.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Well, you know, it's we who ought to be making the fuss.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>Of course you ought to be making a <pb n="53">fuss. Why aren't you, then? You let them just walk out of the house as though it was all as nice as ninepence. And what have you been doing all the morning? Admiring the view, perhaps?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>You aren't being very reasonable, are you?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>Who wants to be reasonable? Here am I, a respectable citizen of Jerusalem, a public official, suddenly made a cockshy for the town. And chiefly because you couldn't keep your own family in order&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>You may not be responsible for what you're saying&mdash;but that's enough. Last night David came here, choosing a time when my father and I were out, because he knew he was forbidden the house. While we were away he made Rachel promise to desert a home where she has had nothing but indulgence. When I caught him at it, and told him what I thought of him, he pretty nearly broke my jaw. Isn't it about time you stopped complaining of your grievances?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>You shouldn't have argued with him&mdash;you should have turned him out.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>He happens to be a bigger man than his father. I don't know how you managed it. Anyway, we might ask you to go with more confidence.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>I warned you, Salathiel, that this was going to happen if you weren't careful. The girl was far too much under the influence of that <pb n="54">mooning brother of yours. If you ask my opinion, he's not quite right in the head.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>We didn't ask your opinion, Barnabas.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>Well, you've got it. <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Isaac again</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>The Master Levi, sir.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Oh, yes.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Isaac shows him in, and goes</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>This is a most unfortunate business, Salathiel.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>You surprise me.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>It's no good being touchy. I've come because I thought you should know at once. A report has reached the Governor that you have allowed your daughter to join the Nazarene.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Whether I allowed it or not, she went.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>A very unfavourable construction is placed upon the incident.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Must you talk like an official report?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>That is not very civil of you, Esther.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>You see, Salathiel.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>You've been no friend of mine, Barnabas&mdash;far from it. But I'll give you a hint. It is suggested that as David's father you are an unfit person for public employment.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>There&mdash;I told you&mdash;<stage>(<hi r="italic">to Salathiel</hi>)</stage> and it's all your fault, you old fool.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Will you please go.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, I'll go. And I hope that when I'm in the mud, you'll be there with me.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">He takes a step to go, when</hi>&mdash;</stage>
<pb n="55">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">First Guard</hi>.</speaker> <p>Look&mdash;what's that&mdash;up there?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Second Guard</hi>.</speaker> <p>By Jove&mdash;yes&mdash;they're coming.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">There is a general movement to the terrace</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">first at the balustrade</hi>).</stage> <p>Yes, it is.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>God&mdash;what a crowd.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>Sweeping over the top of the hill like ants. What a frightful thing to see.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>How near they are, suddenly.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">First Guard</hi>.</speaker> <p>Send the word.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Two Guards together</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">calling down towards the city</hi>).</stage> <p>Stand to! Stand to!</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">The cry is repeated at intervals into the distance</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">standing behind the others</hi>).</stage> <p>I knew they would come.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>What am I to do? Can't somebody tell me what I ought to do?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Forget yourself, if you can.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">shaking the First Guard by the arm</hi>).</stage> <p>What am I to do?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">First Guard</hi>.</speaker> <p>I have no instruction about that, sir. I should sit down and be quiet.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>I shall report you to the Governor.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">First Guard</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, sir. Stand back if you please.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Second Guard</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">to the Guards below</hi>).</stage> <p>All ready?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Voices</hi>.</speaker> <p>All ready.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Listen. All of you&mdash;listen.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">In the silence a distant chanting can be heard</hi>.</stage>
<pb n="56">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>You cannot hear it&mdash;but I can. Hosanna, they cry&mdash;yes&mdash;Hosanna&mdash;to&mdash;the Son&mdash;of David.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>Look&mdash;the people are coming in to the road from the fields.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>They are climbing the trees.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes&mdash;they are breaking down the branches from the palms.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Hosanna, they cry&mdash;Hosanna to the Son of David.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>This is all iniquity.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">to Barnabas</hi>).</stage> <p>And Barnabas was David's father.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>They really ought to close the gate. It's absurd to let a mob come in like that just as it pleases.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>No. The Governor is right. He was telling me last night that he had thought of shutting them out, but had decided against it. After all, it's a free city and it would only have inflamed them.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>Well, in my opinion you're a good deal too tolerant in your ideas, Salathiel. I've noticed it more than once lately. I have no sympathy with all this nonsense about free this and free that. It only makes for anarchy. You shouldn't compromise in your opinions.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I have lost a daughter for my opinions. I sent her out there with bitter words&mdash;words that I shall never forget. Don't talk to me about compromise.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="57">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>All the same, I would shut them out myself, father&mdash;Rachel and all. I should call that a pretty dangerous mob. And it's getting larger as they get nearer.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>It's terrifying. They seem to be coming out of the earth.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Can you see him?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>It's hard to distinguish anything&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>It doesn't sound like a mob&mdash;it's so deep and regular, that cry&mdash;Hosanna&mdash;you hear it&mdash;Hosanna&mdash;Hosanna&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes&mdash;look&mdash;there he is&mdash;riding on the ass.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>They are throwing the branches from the palms down into his path as he passes.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes&mdash;and their garments too&mdash;look, they are spreading their clothes out in the road for him to trample on. They are a lot of hysterical maniacs. What do you suppose is going to happen to me if they start brawling, and my son is mixed up in it?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Who cares a damn what happens to you?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>I do. I'm going home.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">First Guard</hi>.</speaker> <p>No one can leave the house. The streets are to be kept clear.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>There is a little foal trotting beside the ass.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>What does Jesus look like, father? Can you see him?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes. He must be a tall man.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="58">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>You cannot see his hands, can you?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>His hands? No, girl.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>They are quiet hands. I know it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>There'll be a fine scramble when they get down to the gate. There must be over a thousand of them.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">The rhythm of the approaching crowd steadily increases in volume</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>They are very near it now.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">The sound gradually fades</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>What is it?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>They are at the foot of the hill. They are hidden by the gate.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>They are coming through. The Governor must be mad.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">The volume grows again. Isaac comes in</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>If you please, sir.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, Isaac, what is it?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Do you mind, sir, if we come upstairs? We all feel as though we were cooped up in a trap down there.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>As you please.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">Isaac calls in half&hyphen;a&hyphen;dozen servants, who edge out deferentially on to the terrace</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>They are through.</p>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">There is a burst of quite regular chanting</hi>&mdash;</stage>
<p>&ldquo;Hosanna to the Son of David: Blessed is he that cometh in the name of the Lord: Hosanna in the highest.&rdquo;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Look&mdash;he is coming through the gate.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="59">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>He is like one on a pilgrimage.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Is he lovely?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, child, he is lovely.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Why did Rachel know better than I knew?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Mathias&mdash;Mathias&mdash;do you see&mdash;there she is&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>With David&mdash;he will destroy me&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Be quiet, you, Barnabas.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">The sound is surging up to the house</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Second Guard</hi>.</speaker> <p>Those are the fellows they call his disciples, aren't they?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>That lad Jacob there&mdash;look at him&mdash;those must be his brothers.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">crying out</hi>).</stage> <p>Rachel&mdash;Rachel my child!</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Father!&mdash;what's the use of mixing yourself up in&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Be quiet, Mathias&mdash;she is my daughter&mdash;Rachel&mdash;Rachel&mdash;do you hear me?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">First Guard</hi>.</speaker> <p>I shouldn't interfere, sir&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Rachel&mdash;Rachel!</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Does she look very happy&mdash;? I know she does&mdash;I can tell it&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Rachel! Yes, my dear&mdash;look, she has heard me.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">There is a sudden hush below, a few voices in authority calling for silence</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>What is it?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>She is speaking to him&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, and Uncle Nathan too&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="60">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>They have stopped&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>What have they stopped for?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>He is looking up here&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Why can't I see him&mdash;O God&mdash;why can't I see him?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>What does Uncle Nathan want? Look here, father, you can't let him come in&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>No, Salathiel&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">to the Guards</hi>).</stage> <p>Why don't your men tell them to move on? We don't want to have anything to do with them&mdash;we shall all get into trouble over this&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>What must they stop outside here for? In an hour the house will be the scandal of Jerusalem.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan's Voice</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">from below</hi>).</stage> <p>Salathiel!</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Go away, Uncle Nathan&mdash;we don't want you here&mdash;you've done enough harm already&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">speaking down</hi>).</stage> <p>Yes, Nathan&mdash;what is it?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Is Esther there?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">moving out on to the terrace</hi>).</stage> <p>Yes, Uncle Nathan.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>The Master wants to speak to you.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>To me?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Don't be preposterous. There is nothing that Esther wants to hear&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>I will come.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>You'll do nothing of the sort. In any case you can't get by the Guards.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="61">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">First Guard</hi>.</speaker> <p>That's right, miss&mdash;strict orders you know.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Tell him I will come, Uncle Nathan. <stage>(<hi r="italic">She moves across the room</hi>)</stage> I shall go. They dare not touch me.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Esther, my dear&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>It's no use, father&mdash;I must go.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Of course they dare touch you. You've no chance of getting out.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>We shall see.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">She goes, feeling her way certainly from the room</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">on the terrace</hi>).</stage> <p>I told you there would be the devil to pay, and here he is.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>Who is it?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>That officer fellow who was nosing along here last night. I'm going to speak up&mdash;I'll let him know it's no fault of mine.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer's Voice</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">from below</hi>).</stage> <p>No one else is to come into the city. Go up to the gate, and say so.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">A Guard</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">answering</hi>).</stage> <p>Yes, sir.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>And you get as quickly as you can to headquarters. Tell two companies to be in readiness.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Other Guard</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, sir.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>You see, father&mdash;they've spotted us. We might all just as well be down there shouting Hosanna with the rest of them.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>This is what comes of doing good turns. <pb n="62">You'll tell him, Salathiel, that I've nothing to do with all this?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Anything you like, Levi.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">fuming into the room</hi>).</stage> <p>What is going on here? Why are these people halted outside your house?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Are they doing any harm?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>Our orders are to see that they keep on the move. They have chosen your house&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I do not know&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>Of course you know. Last night in this room I asked you&mdash;and that girl of yours was here as I spoke.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I could not&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>You lied.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Roman or no Roman, I will not endure insolence&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>Insolence! C&aelig;sar's arm is long, my friend, and powerful.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I do not care&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Father!</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>Salathiel&mdash;what are you saying&mdash;?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes&mdash;and you, Barnabas&mdash;it was your son&mdash;he was here too&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>I disown him. I came here now to tell Salathiel that I would take no responsibility&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>You will take it, nevertheless. This day, let me tell you, is not over yet, not by a long sight. And, if trouble comes, you&mdash;both of you&mdash;will have to answer for your share in it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="63">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>But we could do nothing&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>There you are, Salathiel&mdash;what did I say? Believe me, sir, I have done all I could to show this miserable boy&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Miserable child! Those were my own words&mdash;do what you will, Rome&mdash;nothing can deepen the bitterness of those words.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">First Guard</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">to the Officer</hi>).</stage> <p>Beg your pardon, sir&mdash;but the other young lady has gone out of the house&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>It's Esther&mdash;she is talking to the man.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>What did you send the Guards away for&mdash;?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>Another of your dutiful children?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Esther&mdash;Esther.</p>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">There is a renewed sound of movement below</hi>.</stage>
<p>&ldquo;Hosanna to the Son of David: Blessed is he&mdash;&rdquo;</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">And the crowd moves on</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>I have warned you. <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">He goes out</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Where is she? I cannot see her. Esther&mdash;Esther!</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>What difference does it make now? I might just as well clear off to the Nile. They forget things there. You have destroyed us, father.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Destruction has lost its meaning, boy.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>What's the use of talking moral posies to me? There's a damned good business ruined. That's all I know.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">to the First Guard</hi>).</stage> <p>I suppose I can go, now they've moved on?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="64">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">First Guard</hi>.</speaker> <p>I have no orders.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>Well, I'm going anyway. There's no one downstairs to stop me now. And for you, Salathiel, if we come up before the Governor together, don't expect any consideration from me. I shall tell the truth straight out.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>That's right, Barnabas.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>And don't be so smug about it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>You really are making rather a fool of yourself, aren't you?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>Whereas you have arranged everything so skilfully.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">The sound of the procession is fading towards Jerusalem</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>They are closing the gate.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">to Barnabas</hi>).</stage> <p>Why don't you go?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi>.</speaker> <p>All right, I'm going. But you'll see&mdash;if I'm in for it, so are you. You're in for it anyway. Your blasted house will have reason to remember this day's work.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">As he moves to go, he is faced by Esther at the entrance</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>This house will have reason to remember it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Barnabas</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">recoiling</hi>).</stage> <p>What's the matter with you?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>You have a mean face, Barnabas. Too mean to be David's father. Go.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Barnabas hurries out, scared</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Esther&mdash;what is it?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="65">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>He has given me back my sight.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">There is an astonished silence as she crosses to her father</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>What do you mean, Esther?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Father, send all these people away.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">awestruck</hi>).</stage> <p>If you please, miss&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>It is all right, Isaac. Take your men downstairs.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">Isaac directs the servants to go. He follows them all, as though leaving the presence of a ghost</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">at a loss</hi>).</stage> <p>Are you talking of miracles?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>No. I was not even surprised. It was nature in those hands. Please do not stay. I am tired. <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Levi goes, bewildered as the others</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Esther&mdash;you mean&mdash;?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>I can see. That is all.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>I always said it would be cured.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes&mdash;you always said it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>What was it&mdash;? <stage>(<hi r="italic">Embracing her</hi>)</stage> Blessed be the God of Israel!</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>It was not Israel's God. It was the Nazarene.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>My child.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>He, too, said &ldquo;My child.&rdquo; He said, &ldquo;Look into my face, my child.&rdquo; There is no other face in the world like that.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>But don't you understand&mdash;the time had come&mdash;it just happened so.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>No, Mathias. It was the Nazarene.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="66">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Why did you not follow him?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>He forbade me. &ldquo;Your father needs you, child,&rdquo; he said. I am sorry that I am tired, father dear. It was as though I were being drawn out of all the quicksands of time.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes. Sit here beside me.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">Quietly she does so, very peacefully resting her head on his shoulder</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">on the terrace, standing between the Guards, looking towards the city</hi>).</stage> <p>They are out of sight. The world is mad.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">gently</hi>).</stage> <p>Hosanna in the highest. Blessed is he that cometh in the name of the Lord.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Hush&hyphen;a&hyphen;by, hush&hyphen;a&hyphen;by. Hosanna to the Son of David.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>You, too, father! Is there no thought anywhere but for the crazy Nazarene?</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">From the hill&hyphen;side comes the sound of the shepherd's pipe</hi>.</stage>
<trailer><hi r="smcap">the curtain falls</hi></trailer>
</div3>
<pb n="67">
<div3>
<comhd3><idref>Z300767887</idref><collection>1 2</collection>
ACT III <attbytes>68Kb</attbytes><display>1</display><reflink></reflink><comcitn><ty>BOOK</ty><id>Z300767887</id><a1>Drinkwater, John, 1882&ndash;1937</a1><t1>A Man's House: A Play in Three Acts</t1><pbl>Sidgwick &amp; Jackson, Ltd.</pbl><y1>1934</y1><t2>Literature Online</t2></comcitn></comhd3>
<stage><p><hi r="italic">The same scene, seven days later&mdash;the first Easter Sunday. It is late afternoon. The quiet sounds still come in from the hill&hyphen;side</hi>.</p>
<p><hi r="italic">Mathias is seated at a table, with papers and a ledger. A Clerk stands by him</hi>.</p></stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">examining a document</hi>).</stage> <p>Yes&mdash;that seems to be in order. <stage>(<hi r="italic">Handing it to the Clerk</hi>)</stage> Get Samuel to check it. See that it is delivered to&hyphen;night.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Clerk</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">taking it</hi>).</stage> <p>Yes, sir. <stage>(<hi r="italic">Turning as he is about to go out</hi>)</stage> By the way, sir, you don't think there's anything in it, do you?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">at his papers</hi>).</stage> <p>In what?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Clerk</hi>.</speaker> <p>A lot of people seem rattled. Something that the Nazarene said about the third day. It's three days, you know, since he was crucified. Dead men can't come back, can they?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Don't listen to such nonsense. And if you must listen, don't bother me about it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Clerk</hi>.</speaker> <p>No, sir. <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">He hurries out</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">Mathias goes on with his work, rather defiantly. After a moment or two Isaac comes in</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>If you please, sir, excuse me&mdash;but why don't you go down and see if you can't do something?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="68">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>I've told you, Isaac&mdash;I've told every&hyphen;body in this house&mdash;I'll have nothing to do with it. They got themselves into this infernal mess&mdash;wilfully. Let them get out of it. If they can.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>I know, sir. But I can't believe they really meant it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Meant it be damned. They assaulted a Roman soldier&mdash;you can't get over that. If Rome objects to having its soldiers assaulted by civilians, I don't blame Rome.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>But Mr Nathan, sir&mdash;he's such a quiet old gentleman&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>My Uncle Nathan, Isaac, is a poet&mdash;or thinks he is. And poets aren't to be trusted.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>You might go down, sir, and see. When our own folk are in trouble&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Are you growing soft, too, Isaac?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>I'm not, sir. But that young Master David began it&mdash;he's a very civil young gentleman really&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Have you felt his fist?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>I beg your pardon, sir?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>I have. He's a hot&hyphen;headed fool.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>But our Miss Rachel must see a lot of good in him.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>A lot of good looks, that's all. If a girl can't control her silly passions, she must take the consequences. She chose to throw us all over for a red&hyphen;headed buffoon with no more balance than a calf. A precious lot of good she's done herself.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="69">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>I know, sir&mdash;I don't hold with their opinions. I think they're crazy. The Nazarene meant nothing to me alive, and he means nothing dead, whatever people may say. But crazy or not, I can't bear to think of what may happen. That boy Jacob, too&mdash;he's just a child&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>It's no good being sentimental about it, Isaac. They couldn't behave themselves, and when you can't behave yourself, you have to be taught.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>They may be scourged for it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>I shouldn't wonder.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Have you ever seen a man scourged, sir?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>No.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>I have. It's terrible. They take him, and&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>I've no wish to hear what they do.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Iasac</hi>.</speaker> <p>It would kill Mr Nathan, sir. I think it would kill the boy, too.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">suddenly flinging his papers aside and rising</hi>).</stage> <p>Well, what the devil do you expect me to do?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Perhaps they might allow you to put in a word for them. The Roman officer gentleman said that if we did everything possible in that way there was some hope&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>The Roman officer gentleman has had his head turned by my sister. He doesn't know what he's talking about.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Miss Esther might do a lot worse.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="70">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">returning to his work</hi>).</stage> <p>Thank you, Isaac. We won't discuss that.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>I beg your pardon, I'm sure, sir.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Esther comes in</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>What's the matter, Isaac?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Matter, miss?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes. What are you so earnest about?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>He was asking me to go down and say what splendid fellows Uncle Nathan and David and the dear little Jacob were to throw bricks at a Roman soldier who was doing his duty.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>It wasn't his duty. He struck a condemned man. You know it wasn't his duty.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">A Servant comes in</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Servant</hi>.</speaker> <p>The Roman officer wishes to see you, sir.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">sharply</hi>).</stage> <p>Tell him&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Bring him up. <stage>(<hi r="italic">The servant goes</hi>)</stage> It's all right, Isaac, you needn't stay.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>I meant no harm, miss. Only if they should&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>There, there, Isaac. Go along.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Isaac goes out</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>What's the use of seeing this fellow?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Probably none. But I happen to like him.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>My sisters have odd tastes.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">at the entrance</hi>).</stage> <p>If you please, sir.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">He goes as the Officer comes in</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, what is it?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>I think it's going to be all right.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="71">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>You mean they'll be acquitted?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>I think so. It has been a near thing, but the crucifixion of Jesus has made them lenient.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Did you give evidence?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Very obliging of you.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>Not obliging. I merely said what I knew.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>That was generous.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>You made me so.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>I don't wish to interfere&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Then don't. This is not your business, Mathias.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Oh, no&mdash;of course not. What my family does is no concern of mine.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>In any case you can leave me out of it. I can look after myself.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Then you're cleverer than my other sister. What's the sense in you two getting sweet on each other&mdash;oh, yes, I know all about it. Rome doesn't want our sort&mdash;and if it comes to that, we don't want Rome.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>Aren't you a little dogmatic?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, I am, and I have good reason to be.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>If you are so interested in your family, why aren't you with those of it who need you?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>I see&mdash;I'm not wanted. All right&mdash;I'll go. But I've told you I'll have nothing to do with that miserable business down there. Father ought to have had more sense, too, after what has <pb n="72">happened. If nobody else cares about keeping this house standing, I do. And it's going to take me all my time. This past week will take a twelve&hyphen;month to live down, even if we're lucky.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>You're all right, anyway.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Who's going to discriminate and say&mdash;&ldquo;Well, Mathias didn't&rdquo;&mdash;when they say Salathiel's family mixed itself up with a man who was executed as a common criminal&mdash;?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Stop that. You know very well that no one thinks he was a common criminal. Our own priests don't believe it&mdash;they destroyed him because they were afraid. Rome doesn't believe it&mdash;Pilate hated doing it&mdash;you know he did.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>That's true. He told me himself that if he could have had his own way it would never have happened.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>It is useless to talk.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Very well. No doubt you'll find other talk more agreeable. <stage>(<hi r="italic">To the Officer</hi>)</stage> I should have thought your reputation&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>Is for me to consider, you were going to say? Yes&mdash;I thank you.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Please don't touch those papers.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">He goes out</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Poor Mathias. It is very difficult for him.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">She goes to a seat on the terrace</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>Of course it's difficult. Everything is&mdash;for everybody.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>You shouldn't come here.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="73">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>I had to.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>It can do no good.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>I tell you I had to, Esther. This week everything has changed for me.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Everything has changed for the world.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>I don't mean that. I can't feel as you do about this man. You can't expect it. But for your sake I've done everything I could.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>I know. It was fine of you.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>It wasn't. We don't do these things because we're fine. We do them passionately, from desire. When I saw you that night, after this wonderful thing had happened to you, I knew that whatever you wanted I must want. I loved you then. I shall love you always.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">slowly</hi>).</stage> <p>Yes, yes. Have they done anything&mdash;said anything?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>When I tried to help a little on Friday at Calvary I was warned to be careful. To&hyphen;day, when I spoke for the old man and the two boys, I was reminded of the warning. Rome will hear about it all right. Presently I shall receive an official notice that it's not my place to take part in provincial politics. I don't suppose they'll do anything more drastic than that.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Just a matter of provincial politics. A blameless man put to death.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>Rome won't regard it as more than that.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>And you?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="74">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes. He was a remarkable man. I confess that I shouldn't have thought about it but for you. But I can understand his influence&mdash;in a way I felt it myself. I think you claim too much for him, though.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>I claim nothing but that he was wiser than the world that killed him. And he had healing hands.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>They were blessed hands, doing what they did.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>That, I know, was how I learnt. He gave me back my life. But I learnt more than my own deliverance. He spoke to the people things that they had never heard.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>I can't dispute with you, Esther. I think Pilate was right in wishing to let him go. Beyond that, I can't say. I only know that you are what no woman has ever been before.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>You are a Roman.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>And then?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Rome crucified him.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>No. It was your own priests.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>They had no choice. It was his authority or theirs. You can't blame them for defending an order that was their life. But for Rome it was different. Rome had no interest to defend. Pilate could have stopped it with a word. He was afraid to speak it. He denied the truth that he knew. You yourself admitted as much.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>You don't understand the difficulties. <pb n="75">We are here to govern by your own laws. We are overseers&mdash;no more than that. Jerusalem demanded the death of this man&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>And so Rome allowed him to be murdered.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>I tell you I protested. What more could I do? I am not Pilate. I don't want&mdash;I want nothing but you.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>A week ago, if anyone had told me that I could refuse a lover for any faith on earth, I should have known him for a fool. And now&mdash;what now? I see you, woman to man, and I am no longer blind. Roman and Jew&mdash;that's nothing. I am caught, as you are. But you killed him&mdash;no&mdash;it was so&mdash;your kind killed him. The ages could not make me forget that. He spoke to me&mdash;down there&mdash;a week ago&mdash;and now&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>What's the use of talking about it like this? I don't even know what your words mean. Some day, perhaps&mdash;we might sit together discussing it all&mdash;but not now. I love you. I know nothing but that, I want to know nothing. You say that you are caught as I am. Bless you for that. Don't you see that there is but one way of escape? <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">He takes her hands in his</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Please don't.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>Why not?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Because there is the shadow of a cross between us.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>It shall not be.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">He draws her to him. After a moment of <pb n="76">hesitation, her nature takes possession, and she attempts no further refusal</hi>.</stage>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">Releasing herself, radiant yet apprehensive, she goes out on to the terrace</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>And what is to happen now?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>You will marry me.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>You have taken risks already. What would Rome say to this?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>I know. But I am tired of Jerusalem anyway, and I have money. I can buy my discharge, and I have a little farm on the Adriatic&mdash;it would keep us. Will you go?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Don't ask me now. I love you. That is enough. <stage>(<hi r="italic">Isaac comes in</hi>)</stage> Yes, Isaac?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>The master has just come in, miss. He asked for Mr Mathias. Do you know where he is? I thought he was up here. I think there's something the matter.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>He went downstairs.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>He must have gone out.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>What do you mean, something the matter?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>The master looks troubled, miss&mdash;not as though everything had gone all right.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Salathiel comes in</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>What is it, father?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Where is Mathias?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>He was here a few minutes ago.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">as Isaac makes to leave</hi>).</stage> <p>You can stay, Isaac. You may as well hear.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>It's nothing bad, is it, sir?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="77">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">to Esther</hi>).</stage> <p>They took your Uncle Nathan's age into consideration, and bound him over to keep the peace. David is free, but he is ordered to leave Jerusalem within a week. The boy Jacob is sentenced to the galleys.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Oh, sir!</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>But that is monstrous. Why?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>It was only against him that evidence of actual assault was given.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>But when I left the court&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I know&mdash;it was just at the end&mdash;that ferret&hyphen;eyed notary made a plea of public security that alarmed them again.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Can nothing be done?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>David will have to go.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>And the boy, sir?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I offered to take him back into my employment. They said that only a Roman could do that.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">to the Officer</hi>).</stage> <p>Couldn't you&mdash;we&mdash;?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>I'll go at once to Pilate. There is an old score between us&mdash;he won't refuse.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">He goes, followed by Isaac</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>We? What did you mean by we?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>He wants me to marry him.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Nonsense.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, that's one way of looking at it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>But you don't mean&mdash;?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>I mean nothing at the moment. Where are David and Rachel?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="78">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>They are coming here. I couldn't speak to them, but I left word.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>To stay?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Until he leaves Jerusalem.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>You mean until they leave.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>How can she go?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>She is his wife. Do you expect her to desert him at the first mishap? She didn't go to him like that.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Now understand, Esther&mdash;I won't have you encouraging her to go away. What's come over you all? It isn't reasonable. A month ago this was a rational, contented household. Now what are we? Rachel has tied herself up to a convicted rebel, Mathias has turned against me, and you want to go off with a Roman.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, everything has changed.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Why did the Nazarene come?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>It was ordained.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I know. Hosanna&mdash;yes, child, and for you above all. But my house was so safe&mdash;I was so proud of it. And it is falling.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>But these things are common. If Rachel and I go, you will settle down again with Mathias.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>He thinks I've been weak about it all. I suppose I have. A business can't afford to be mixed up in this kind of thing. Nearly half our accounts have been closed already. I don't blame him for being bitter.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>People very soon forget.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="79">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I don't think this is going to be soon forgotten. No; the storm has shaken us. <stage>(<hi r="italic">A pause</hi>)</stage> You can't marry this Roman.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Why not? He loves me. And I don't think I could stay here after all that has happened. I must go far away from those dreadful hours on Calvary. <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Mathias returns</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Father&mdash;David and Rachel are coming up the road. I've heard all about the judgments. They're not coming here?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Of course they can't.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>They must. Where else can they go?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>I don't know anything about that, but they can't come here. You must see that.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>But Mathias&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Please&mdash;Esther. If you want to make a fool of yourself with a Roman, you must, but there's going to be no more nonsense in this house. I've been through enough this week to break my nerve&mdash;but it's not going to be broken. I'm going to fight to recover what's lost, and I don't care who comes in my way. If you won't see plain sense about this, father, I must. David is an outlaw, and lucky at that. Rachel has made her choice, and she must stand by it. We're pretty near ruin as it is, and that would finish it. I won't have them here, do you understand. I won't have it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Mathias&mdash;I am master&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>No, you're not. If things get any <pb n="80">worse there'll be nothing to be master of. I'm going to stop them from getting worse, and it seems I've got to do it alone. Very well, but there's going to be no more fooling about it. You will tell them that they can't stay&mdash;I insist.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Mathias&mdash;you make it very hard&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>I make it hard? I like that. Hard for whom? What about me? What earthly good has this done for anybody, except Esther, who as I tell you could have been cured by a competent doctor in any case. I see a decent household and a prosperous business being demoralised and broken up by an impostor who has been properly exposed, and because I'm the only one to lift a hand I'm told I make it hard. <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Isaac comes in</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Miss Rachel and Master David are just coming, sir&mdash;what am I to do?&mdash;Mr Mathias says I'm not to let them in.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Go and let them in at once, of course&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>I say it's preposterous&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Don't be absurd, Mathias. We can't shut the door in Rachel's face. Let them in, Isaac.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, miss. <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">He goes</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Let's be clear about it. If they stay I go. But if you drive me out of the house, you sha'n't drive me out of the business. There's not one of our connections who wouldn't stand by me, and they shall know I'm rid of the lot of you.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>No one wants to drive you out of the house, my boy.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="81">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Well, you can't have me and David, or Rachel either. <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Rachel and David come in</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">embracing her</hi>).</stage> <p>Rachel, my child. <stage>(<hi r="italic">Taking David's hand as Rachel kisses Esther</hi>)</stage> I am sorry.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>You should be angry.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes. But I am not. Only sorry, for us all.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">moving to Mathias</hi>).</stage> <p>Well, Mathias.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">to Rachel and David</hi>).</stage> <p>Listen, you two. My father has lost grip on things. I'm sorry to say it, but he has. Our family has stood for something in Jerusalem since it was founded here seven generations ago. I mean it to stand for something still, and there's no room for cheap martyrdoms in this house. This Nazarene business means nothing to responsible people. He has paid for his folly, and I don't want to argue about it. But our name can stand no more of it, so please go where you will, and take it with you.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>It's all right, Mathias, we're going.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>But, Rachel&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>No, father&mdash;we've made up our minds. It's dear of you to wish it, but Mathias is right. It wouldn't be fair to him if we stayed. We only came back to thank you, and say good&hyphen;bye.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>But where are you going?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>I have friends in Damascus.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>It's a long way. I shall never see you again, Rachel.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="82">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>There, father&mdash;don't let us make it more difficult. But now&mdash;about Uncle Nathan&mdash;you must let him come back again.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>But that's just as bad. Everyone knows he was in this scandal as much as any of you.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>But you couldn't turn an old man like that away.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>What is it to do with you?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Nothing&mdash;but it's common humanity. He's a fine old man&mdash;you can't let him go adrift&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>You needn't tell me what I can and can't do. Put it bluntly, I'm thinking only of myself. My only chance is to be clear of the lot of you. <stage>(<hi r="italic">With fingers on his own wrist</hi>)</stage> I can feel the pulse of my fortune to half a beat. The Nazarene was a distemper of which my reputation must be purged&mdash;you understand? I can't afford to be compromised with any friend of his.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Your Uncle Nathan must stay in my house if I wish it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>I tell you he shan't. He was associated with a felon.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Mathias, you mustn't speak like that.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Who was it on Calvary but a felon?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>It is a wicked lie.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>David!</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Don't alarm yourself, Rachel. You should know him by now.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>You mustn't call the Master a felon.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="83">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>And if I do?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>You won't.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">her hand on his arm</hi>).</stage> <p>David&mdash;David&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Or you will strike me again in the name of Christ. The Prince of Peace you call him, don't you? <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Nathan appears at the doorway</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>The Prince of Peace. My sons!</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Why do you come back here?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>I came to say good&hyphen;bye.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>You can stay here, Nathan&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>You can't&mdash;it isn't reasonable&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>No, Mathias, it isn't reasonable. I came, too, about the boy Jacob. Salathiel, can nothing be done?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>The Roman who spoke for you in court has gone to see.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Do you know who he is?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>How do you mean? He was here that night before the Nazarene came down from Bethany. He has been very considerate since.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>He was on Calvary.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>He has asked, me to marry him, Uncle Nathan.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>A Roman? And yet you should. He is a very noble man. Yes; he, too, was on Calvary.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>I thought it must be the same man.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>What man?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>In the last agony of crucifixion&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Isaac at the door</hi>.</stage>
<pb n="84">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>The Master Levi, sir. Shall I bring him up?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes. <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Isaac goes</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>What were you saying, David?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Do you love him, Esther?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, Uncle Nathan, I love him.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Then&mdash;<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Isaac with Levi</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>The Master Levi, sir. <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Isaac goes</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>What is it, Levi?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>Have you heard?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>What?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>It's all over Jerusalem.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>What's all over Jerusalem?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>They say that the Nazarene has risen from the dead.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">after a moment's silence</hi>).</stage> <p>It is the third day.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Everyone knows what has happened. I heard of it in the city just now. His disciples stole his body from the tomb where some fanatic from Arimathea had placed it by Pilate's leave. It's all part of the imposture.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">with severe self&hyphen;control</hi>).</stage> <p>Rachel, let us go.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>It is said that some of the women have seen him.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>There's no sense in repeating hysterical nonsense like that.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Calling it that won't dispose of it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>You go away with your friends, Rachel, and make as much of it as you like. But some of us <pb n="85">mean to go on with our lives like rational beings. I do, for one. I've no use for moonshine about dead men being alive. Enough heads have been turned by this business already. Well, it's over. Let's forget about it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>It has only just begun.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>&ldquo;After three days I shall rise again.&rdquo; Those were his words.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">at his papers</hi>).</stage> <p>If you don't mind, all of you, I have business to attend to. I don't know what your plans may be, but we needn't discuss them further here, need we?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Let us leave decisions until to&hyphen;morrow. We shall see more clearly then. It is time for dinner. Will you join us, Levi?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>Thank you.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>We must go to&hyphen;night.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>No&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, father, it is better so.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>We will go, Salathiel.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>No, Nathan, you at least must stay.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Mathias is right, father. It is impossible for us to stay.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I will not have it. I will not be left alone. Mathias, don't you see what you are doing? You yourself say that this Nazarene affair is nothing. In a few weeks Jerusalem will remember nothing of it. And when it is forgotten, you will have taken from me half the meaning of my old age. My daughters will be exiles, beyond my call.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="86">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>But Rachel has to go in any case, father. And you could hardly keep me here with a Roman husband.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>You must see that Esther is speaking sense.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes. I see. You are determined to take them from me. Nathan, will you not stay? If I ask it? If I ask it with all my heart? You owe me some consideration, don't you?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>I shall never forget how much.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Then stay.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>It would not help you.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Why do you keep on asking, father?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Because I am afraid of you, Mathias.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>You should be afraid of everyone but me. <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">The Roman Officer returns</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes&mdash;where is he?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>Downstairs.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>You managed it then. I'm glad of that.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>I can't say that he seems too grateful. I had to bring him away by the scruff of his neck.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>How do you mean?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>Pilate was quite reasonable&mdash;he gave the order at once. But the boy created a regular scene&mdash;swore he wouldn't come&mdash;said he hated the sight of Romans. Of course they bore no malice against the silly child&mdash;they were glad to get rid of him. But they had to kick him out, and he was a handful to get up here, I don't mind telling you. <pb n="87">A fine spectacle we made in the street coming along&mdash;people thought I was abducting him. I knew he was a tough customer when he began making a fuss on Friday. I'm not for sending youngsters like that to the galleys, but if you ask me he's been pretty near getting no more than he deserves.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">The voices of Isaac and Jacob are heard on the stairs outside</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>You've been in enough trouble, my lad.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>I don't care&mdash;I will go up&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Leave well alone, you little fool&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>Take your hands off me&mdash;I'm not going to stand this.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>It'll serve you right if he'll have nothing more to do with you&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>I don't want him to have anything to do with me&mdash;let me go, I say&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">Jacob bursts into the room, followed by Isaac</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>Look here&mdash;let me get out of this. Isaac has shut me in&mdash;he tried to do that once before&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>You'll do as you are told&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>I won't&mdash;and I don't want any of your dirty Roman charity either&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Have you taken leave of your senses?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>I daresay I have. Who wouldn't after what happened up there on Calvary? Why aren't you all out of your senses?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Jacob, my boy&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>No&mdash;it's no use, sir. You've been a good <pb n="88">master to me&mdash;but that means nothing any more. Nothing means anything any more. Let them send me to the galleys. I'd rather be there, or dead, than anywhere.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>But this gentleman wants to help you&mdash;to give you a new life that you can be proud of. I'm going with him.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>He's a Roman, and the Romans killed him. It was a Roman who struck him going up the hill&mdash;I threw a stone in his smug Roman face. If they hadn't held me, I would have throttled him. Let me go.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>For God's sake let him go.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>My son&mdash;you loved the Master who is dead?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>I worship him.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>He would not wish you to behave like this.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>I can't forget the things they did to him.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>You needn't forget. But we must remember him with service, not despair. You are young, you have many years in which to speak his name. To take this punishment, wilfully, would help neither you nor him. Go to this new work. It is kindly offered, and Miss Esther wishes it. She will be there.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">to Esther</hi>).</stage> <p>Why are you going with a Roman?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>I am going to marry him.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>Why?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="89">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>This is monstrous. Are you all going to let yourselves be cross&hyphen;examined by a boy out of the kitchen? Go&mdash;get to your galleys and have done with it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>His life is as important as yours, Mathias. <stage>(<hi r="italic">To Jacob</hi>)</stage> I shall marry him because he is the best man I know.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>A Roman?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>This Roman did a great service to the Master, my son.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>Please&mdash;let us have none of that.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>A service?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>No word is ever to be spoken of that.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>What was it? You were not the man&mdash;?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">authoritatively</hi>).</stage> <p>Be silent.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Rachel, we must go.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Not to&hyphen;night&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, father, it is better. Another night would make it no easier for any of us. Good&hyphen;bye.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">embracing her</hi>).</stage> <p>Good&hyphen;bye, my child. Bless you&mdash;bless you.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>There may be a day yet&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>No&mdash;I shall never see you again.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Good&hyphen;bye, Esther.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">kissing her</hi>).</stage> <p>Good&hyphen;bye.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">to Salathiel</hi>).</stage> <p>Good&hyphen;bye, sir. I am sorry.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">taking his hand</hi>).</stage> <p>Good&hyphen;bye. Love her. And bless you, too.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="90">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Good&hyphen;bye, Mathias.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Good&hyphen;bye. When you have gone, I shall wish you good luck.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Uncle Nathan, you have always been a darling to me&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>My dear, I am going to ask what you will not refuse. Let me come with you.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>But we are going to face a world of hardships.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi>.</speaker> <p>I fear none. I can sing. We will serve him together.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>As you will.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Rachel</hi>.</speaker> <p>We will look after each other.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Mathias, you can afford to bear no grudge. <stage>(<hi r="italic">To the Officer</hi>)</stage> Thank you, and good luck to you both.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Nathan</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">kissing Esther</hi>).</stage> <p>My blessing on you. <stage>(<hi r="italic">To Salathiel</hi>)</stage> And on your house, my brother.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>It is desolate.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>It is rising from the flames.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, my boy.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">David</hi>.</speaker> <p>Come, Rachel.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">She goes, then David and Nathan. Isaac is about to follow them</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Isaac.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, sir.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>My little cedar box. At once.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, sir. <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">He goes</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">to Esther</hi>).</stage> <p>What are you going to do?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>We, too, must go.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="91">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Go? But how&mdash;?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>I told Pilate. I have his authority. These things are better done at once.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>You spare me nothing, none of you. Go, then.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Isaac returns, giving the box to Salathiel</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">unlocking it, and taking out a bag of money</hi>).</stage> <p>Go after them with this. Say it is my last request. Take no refusal. <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Isaac obeys</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">to the Officer</hi>).</stage> <p>What was it you did for the Master?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>Some day perhaps I will tell you.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>I suppose Mr Nathan was right. I will go with you, Miss Esther.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">to the Officer</hi>).</stage> <p>When you were in the city just now, did you hear anything of this new rumour?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>What rumour?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>That the Nazarene has risen from the dead.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>No, I did not hear it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>They say that his body was not in the tomb when his disciples went this morning.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>I tell you&mdash;they moved it themselves.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>And that some of the women had seen him. One story is that he was not really dead when the man from Arimathea took him down from the cross. That seems the most likely explanation.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>That is impossible.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Why impossible?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>Because&mdash;<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">He stops short</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="92">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>Then you were the man.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>What do you mean? What is it? Tell me&mdash;you must.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>I know. It was in the Master's last agony. He pierced his side.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">to the Officer</hi>).</stage> <p>You&mdash;!</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>No, miss&mdash;it was merciful. It was done in pity. <stage>(<hi r="italic">He throws himself at the Officer's feet</hi>)</stage> I will be faithful to you.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>You killed him&mdash;you, with your own hand&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Jacob</hi>.</speaker> <p>But don't you see, Miss Esther, it was to spare him&mdash;</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>It was a simple kindness.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Where are you and Esther going?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>To my Adriatic farm.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes. You will doubtless have long evenings there in which to discuss it all.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Isaac returns</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>You gave it to them?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, sir. They told me to thank you. They seemed happy.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>I am glad they are happy. Please have dinner served.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes sir. <stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">He goes</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>Esther, you understand?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, I understand.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>I meant never to speak of it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>It is best that I should know. And now, father, good&hyphen;bye.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="93">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Good&hyphen;bye, Esther. There's no more to say.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">The Officer</hi>.</speaker> <p>Good&hyphen;bye, sir.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Good&hyphen;bye.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Esther</hi>.</speaker> <p>All's well, Mathias?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, all's well.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">Esther goes, followed by the Officer and Jacob. Salathiel goes out on to the terrace</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>I think you've been quite right, Mathias.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">at his papers</hi>).</stage> <p>Yes. I have.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>And you may count on our custom. If there should be any pressure&mdash;temporarily&mdash;our credit is at your disposal. It is a substantial one.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Thank you. I shall remember. We shall hold our heads up in Jerusalem yet.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>As never before&mdash;I am sure of it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, as never before.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">from the terrace</hi>).</stage> <p>Nathan walks well beside them.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>Nathan?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes&mdash;half&hyphen;way up the hill to Bethany. I suppose Bethany one day now will be talked of.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Father, don't go dreaming. <stage>(<hi r="italic">He rises and goes out to him on the terrace</hi>)</stage> There&mdash;we'll make all right. It had to be this way. I care for you no less than they did. Have courage with me.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, my son. My only son. When all is said, that is best&mdash;to have a son.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>I won't fail you. <stage>[<hi r="italic">He returns to his work</hi>.</stage></p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="94">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>And, by the way, the Smyrna bank has asked me to recommend a responsible house in Jerusalem. May I name you?</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Smyrna? But of course. That connection is what we most need.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>I will arrange it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Smyrna. That's marvellous. You're something like a friend, Levi.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>I know merit when I see it.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Esther is on the hill, too, with her Roman.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Isaac</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">at the door</hi>).</stage> <p>Dinner is ready, sir.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">He goes</hi>.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>You go with Levi, father. Don't wait for me. I have these figures to finish. I shan't be long.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, Mathias. All my people, going up to Bethany. Rachel and David and Nathan, there. And then Esther and the Roman and Jacob. Going up to Bethany. Yes, just six of them. And the other day there was a multitude. But they were coming down. And now, six people on the road. Six people out of my life.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Father, do go down to dinner.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>No&mdash;not six&mdash;Rachel and David and Nathan, and Esther and the Roman, and Jacob&mdash;that's six&mdash;but, look, there are seven. Who is that following them? Mathias&mdash;Mathias&mdash;it is the Nazarene.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Nonsense, father. Go down with Levi.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="95">
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi></speaker> <stage>(<hi r="italic">coming into the room</hi>).</stage> <p>It is not nonsense, Mathias. The Nazarene is going up the hill to Bethany with them, I tell you.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>Yes, father&mdash;just as you please. I shall be with you in a few minutes.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>Come, Levi. It was the Nazarene.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Levi</hi>.</speaker> <p>We cannot tell about these things.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Salathiel</hi>.</speaker> <p>No. Don't be long, Mathias.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker><hi r="italic">Mathias</hi>.</speaker> <p>No, father.</p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">Salathiel and Levi go</hi>.</stage>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">On the evening stillness comes a faint sound of</hi> Hosanna&mdash;Hosanna in the Highest.</stage>
<stage align="l">[<hi r="italic">Mathias rises and draws the terrace screen, and goes back to his figures</hi>.</stage>
</div3>
